HERECOMEGEORGIEBOY bumped with inner rival early, settled three wide, bid four deep on the far turn and led exiting the turn, lost command in upper stretch, stayed on gamely through the lane but was outfinished by the winner. WORKDAY sped clear and crossed over, set the pace under pressured in the middle stages, vied with a trio of rivals on the far turn, lost command leaving the turn, regained command in upper stretch, inched ahead in the furlong ground and got overtaken by the top pair in the final moments. STAR PROSPECT got put in tight, bumped, then pulled and became a bit rank, chased three wide, mid-pack up the backstretch, bid three deep on the far turn and got outkicked in the late stages. HONDO CROUCH bumped early then steadied briefly and began to pull, went up to press between then outside the pacesetter, challenged between rivals on the far turn, fought through the lane but got outkicked in the final sixteenth. DO IT FOR DAVE got bumped and shuffled early, started to pull and steadied on the first turn, steadied at the three-eighths pole, spun three wide into the lane and lacked a rally. MICKEY GOLDMILL dropped back and trailed two wide into the first turn, raced three deep into the second bend, came four wide into the stretch and failed to menace. BUCK OWENS bumped lightly with a rival and got put in tight quarters between foes early, got blocked behind tiring rival and checked hard entering the far turn, moved to the inside and was not a factor. MY RANSOM raced up close three deep early, started to weaken into the far turn, dropped back around the bend, tired in the lane, eased and walked off.
